or: #1e293b; line-height: 1.75;\">A single P/E multiple is a snapshot. Analyst revision trend is the <em>signal</em>. Today's live example: Roth Capital lowered CAPR's price target from $43 to $38 — but kept the BUY rating. Knowing why the revision happened matters more than the revision itself. Roth wasn't cutting because the FDA data got worse; they cut because the NS Pharma commercial dispute removed an expected $80M milestone payment from their model. Commercial model revision ≠ regulatory thesis revision. The FDA review is unchanged. The $49.67 consensus average still implies +160% from today's price. The lesson: always ask whether an analyst revision is changing the fundamental thesis or just adjusting the commercial model. For binary catalyst plays like CAPR, the regulatory thesis is all that matters before the AdCom. The NS Pharma dispute becomes relevant after approval, when commercial ramp is the driver.</p>\n            <p style=\"margin: 12px 0 0 0; font-size: 12px; color: #475569; font-style: italic;\">Also today: <em>Beat-and-raise</em> — when a company beats earnings AND raises guidance. NFLX proved why this matters: EPS beat isn't enough. No revenue beat + no guidance raise = no beat-and-raise = stock sells off 10%. Watch this exact pattern for META on July 29.</p>\n          </td></tr></table>\n        </td></tr>\n\n        <!-- FOOTER -->\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 4px 24px 24px 24px; border-top: 1px solid #f3f4f6;\">\n          <p style=\"margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-size: 10px; color: #9ca3af; line-height: 1.6;\">Research output, not financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Verify halal compliance quarterly. Generated Sunday July 19, 2026 ~06:00 Kuwait time (UTC+3). This is an automated routine check.</p>\n          <p style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 10px; color: #9ca3af; line-height: 1.6;\">Prices: Yahoo Finance (web search fallback) — last trading close Fri Jul 18, 2026. CAPR $19.10 (range confirmed $18.66–$19.79); prev close $19.44 (Thu Jul 17). Buffett Indicator 237.9%: GuruFocus Jul 17. S&amp;P Forward P/E 20.88x: GuruFocus Jul 17. META/AMZN/NVDA earnings dates: multiple sources confirmed.</p>\n        </td></tr>\n\n      </table>\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>\n"}